01:31:07.777 --> 01:31:08.548
Yes.

01:31:08.548 --> 01:31:09.214
PROFESSOR: Yeah.

01:31:15.450 --> 01:31:16.650
OK, good.

01:31:16.650 --> 01:31:21.900
So you look at here-- yeah.

01:31:21.900 --> 01:31:25.140
Again, r goes from
0 to infinity.

01:31:25.140 --> 01:31:27.160
But this r is very
different from this r now.

01:31:27.160 --> 01:31:29.720
OK?

01:31:29.720 --> 01:31:35.020
So in this definition,
tau is a polar coordinate.

01:31:35.020 --> 01:31:38.360
So in this definition, tau
will go from 0 to 2 pi.

01:31:38.360 --> 01:31:40.170
OK?

01:31:40.170 --> 01:31:46.135
But once you write it in this
form, nothing depends on tau.

01:31:46.135 --> 01:31:49.040
So you can extend tau
to any range you want.

01:31:49.040 --> 01:31:50.870
So once we write
this form, we take

01:31:50.870 --> 01:31:55.890
tau goes to minus
infinity to plus infinity.

01:31:55.890 --> 01:32:01.480
So this is [INAUDIBLE],
